Rev. Esther Abimbola Ajayi, better known as Mama Adura, has a wish for the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Enoch Adeboye. It is no longer news that the highly respected Adeboye marked his 80th birthday on Wednesday and tributes are still pouring in for him. Mama Adura and her husband, Rev. (Dr.) Ademuyiwa Ajayi, also reserved special praises for the GO.   The envoy and a plate full of trouble     Between Makinde and the EFCC     Controversy over ‘mysterious disappearance’ of 21-year-old…   Mama Adura said, “Happy birthday to you, sir, and many happy returns. By the time you turn 90, 100, 110, 120, and 130, as the good Lord leads, we will still be here to celebrate you in good health. May the power of the Holy Spirit continue to be with you. He will never leave or forsake you.” Similarly, her husband said they appreciated all Adeboye has done for them. He commended Adeboye’s wife, Foluke, for taking good care of him. Mama Adura and her husband also sang a birthday song for the pastor.